    <h2>About Us</h2>
    <h3>how we met</h3>

    <p>Jim and Pam. Ben and Leslie. Conrad and Kristina. Either we're destined for our own NBC sitcom or there's something to be said about office romances. Conrad and I met at work and while our paths rarely crossed professionally, we always managed to find ourselves in each other's company - usually at a bar during happy hour. </p>

    <p>On one particular occasion, the happy hour regulars wound up at Benchmark in Old Town and I very distinctly remember three things: I was late, I didn't know what to order, and Conrad came to my rescue with a drink menu. This was when I learned that he had excellent taste in beer (meaning he liked what I liked), so I ordered what he was having, Le Fin du Monde. Things somehow quickly escalated from a friendly cheers to someone challenging someone else to go beer for beer. Probably not the best idea with a 9% beer seeing as how we all found ourselves at a very questionable dance club, but I like to think that if it weren't for a little bit of that liquid courage, we wouldn't have ended the night with plans for our first date...at a scotch bar, no less. </p>

    <p>The rest is history but plenty of drinks and four years later, there's still no one else in this world I'd rather go beer for beer for with.</p>
